{"title": "How to rotate bits to the left and add rotated bits to the right", "tags": ["c", "algorithm", "rotation", "bit-manipulation"], "creation_date": 1477227767, "score": 0, "body": "<pre><code>MSB = (n &gt;&gt; (NUM_OF_BITS_IN_INT - 1))\nn = (n &lt;&lt; 1) | MSB;\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Left bit rotation of <code>n</code> by 1 bit.</p>\n\n<p>You are just shrugging off the MSB but not <em>adding</em> it back at LSB position.</p>\n", "last_activity_date": 1477228140, "answer_id": 40203229, "is_accepted": false, "owner": {"user_id": 1465553, "reputation": 1444, "user_type": "registered", "accept_rate": 75, "display_name": "Saurav Sahu", "link": "http://stackoverflow.com/users/1465553/saurav-sahu", "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5b559f395549789c041652429444dc0a?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG"}, "last_edit_date": 1477228140, "question_id": 40203169}